🌐 Computer Networks
1️⃣ Subnetting (🔥 MOST ASKED)
Simple Idea

Subnetting means dividing a network into smaller networks.

Mental Model (Apartment Building 🏢)

Imagine one big building:

Whole building → Network

Each floor → Subnet

Each room → Device

Instead of chaos, everything becomes organized.

Why It Works

Without subnetting:

Too many devices → congestion

difficult to manage

With subnetting:
✔ better performance
✔ easier management
✔ improved security

Example
192.168.1.0/24

Split into:

192.168.1.0/26

192.168.1.64/26

etc.

Connection to What You Know

Like arrays splitting into subarrays.

Memory Trick 🧠

Subnet = Small network inside big network

2️⃣ NAT (Network Address Translation)
Simple Idea

NAT allows multiple devices to share one public IP.

Mental Model (Hostel WiFi 🏠)

50 students → one WiFi router

All use same public IP

Outside world sees 1 identity, inside there are many.

Why It Works

Because IPv4 addresses are limited.

Real Example

Your home:

Laptop

Phone

TV

All share one IP.

Memory Trick

NAT = Many devices → One public identity

3️⃣ Flow Control
Simple Idea

Flow control ensures sender doesn’t overwhelm receiver.

Mental Model (Teacher & Student 🎓)

Teacher speaks too fast → student can’t understand.

So teacher adjusts speed.

Why It Works

Receiver has limited processing capacity.

Example

TCP uses:

sliding window mechanism

Memory Trick

Flow Control = Speed control of data

4️⃣ Congestion Control
Simple Idea

Prevents network from getting overloaded.

Mental Model (Traffic Jam 🚦)

Too many cars → roads get congested → slow movement.

Same happens in networks.

Why It Works

If too many packets are sent:

packet loss

delays

network crash

Techniques

Slow start

Congestion avoidance

Memory Trick

Congestion = Traffic jam in network

🌍 Social Networks
